Chinnor coach wants settled side
Chinnor coach Jason Bowers feels consistency will be the key to success in National Three South this season.
The Oxfordshire club have won only one of their first seven games but Bowers told BBC Oxford he remains confident they can improve.
Bowers said: "When we got promotion last season, for a long time we had a settled side."
"But this season I have not yet been able to choose the same players in any one game."
I have not yet been able to choose the same players in any one game
Jason Bowers
Chinnor are next in action at Canterbury on 1 November and Bowers feels they are playing well enough to triumph.
"We need a bit of luck but we are playing really well and need that to continue," he explained. "What we need now is just to get a win and hopefully that will kick start our season."
